Problem:
class HealthMonitor {
    private int heartRate;
    private boolean isExerciseActive;

    public HealthMonitor() {
        heartRate = 70; // average resting heart rate
        isExerciseActive = false;
    }

    public void startExercise() {
        isExerciseActive = true;
        increaseHeartRate(30); // Increases heart rate by 30 beats per minute during exercise
    }

    public void stopExercise() {
        isExerciseActive = false;
        decreaseHeartRate(30);
    }

    private void increaseHeartRate(int increment) {
        heartRate += increment;
    }

    private void decreaseHeartRate(int decrement) {
        heartRate -= decrement;
    }

    public int getHeartRate() {
        return heartRate;
    }
}",

If we observe a change in heart rate, can we infer a change in exercise status?
